      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
         <p>The papers of Jacob Gerhard Koch span the years 1783-1941 with the
		  bulk of the material concentrated in the period 1783-1839. They consist of
		  correspondence, letterbooks, diary, account books, ledgers, inventories,
		  indexes, receipts, memoirs of Charles Nicholas Buck published in 1941, and
		  miscellaneous documents. </p>
         <p>The collection relates chiefly to Kochâ€™s business dealings as a
		  merchant and marine insurance broker in Amsterdam, 1787-1790, Alexandria,
		  Virginia, 1790-1792, and Philadelphia, 1792-1817, and reflects his varied
		  business dealings in North America, Europe, and Latin America. Much of the
		  collection is in Dutch, although Koch also wrote in English and French. The
		  diary documents a trip by Koch to Paris, 1817-1818, and reflects Parisian
		  social life as well as financial transactions. Additional material in the
		  collection refers to the liquidation of Kochâ€™s estate following his death in
		  1830.</p>
      </scopecontent>
